url.imageAlt: A newspaper clipping which includes a photo of a theatre with a big sign that says “Princess” and a heading and caption that reads as follows: “Windsor’s New Theatre: Exterior view of the Princess Theatre, Windsor’s new theatre, located on Sandwich street east. It has an attractive front that makes big improvement in the appearance of the street”

description: In 1915, the Princess Theatre hosted Miss Nellie Brook doing an impersonation of Harry Lauder, and a performance by Rollin and Guise, titled “Are They Male or Female? The Sensation of Two Continents”.
